{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_018pRKg97bHMXV1qzPy5cxLP","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"I see the issue. Pod 0 is running but not \"ready\" (the readiness probe is failing), so the StatefulSet won't start pods 1 and 2. The pods need to all start first, and then we run `cockroach init`. But the StatefulSet waits for each pod to be ready before starting the next.\n\nThe readiness probe is hitting `/health?ready=1` which requires the cluster to be initialized. The cluster can't be initialized until all 3 nodes are available, but all 3 nodes won't start until each previous one is \"ready\".\nThe fix is to change the readiness probe to use `/health` instead of `/health?ready=1`. The `/health` endpoint returns 200 even before initialization, while `/health?ready=1` returns 503 until after `cockroach init` runs. This will let all three pods start up, and then I can run the initialization command.\n\nAlternatively, I could set `podManagementPolicy: Parallel` on the StatefulSet so all pods start simultaneously regardless of readiness status—that's probably the cleanest approach here.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":640,"cache_read_input_tokens":31802,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":640},"output_tokens":32,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"c53298a9-31cb-4521-9a59-72bab993213d","uuid":"5c93d58b-f6ac-467e-99f1-9fb7a5994f58","request_id":"req_011CcLUHc3mWbMUe32JE1hia"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_018pRKg97bHMXV1qzPy5cxLP","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The readiness probe blocks pod-1 and pod-2 from starting because pod-0 can't pass `/health?ready=1` until the cluster is initialized — but init requires all 3 nodes. I'll fix the readiness probe to use `/health` (pre-init 200), and add `podManagementPolicy: Parallel` so all pods start concurrently."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":640,"cache_read_input_tokens":31802,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":640},"output_tokens":32,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"c53298a9-31cb-4521-9a59-72bab993213d","uuid":"db1fa155-f44d-4d24-89d1-6a214f4a3e9d","request_id":"req_011CcLUHc3mWbMUe32JE1hia"}
