{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01E3MwU6XLAspAbMkNf2Dfv7","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The 3-node CockroachDB cluster is fully deployed and healthy. Here's a summary of what was created:\n\n**Resources deployed:**\n- `Service/crdb-cluster` — headless service (ClusterIP: None), ports 26257 + 8080, used for pod DNS and peer discovery\n- `Service/crdb-cluster-public` — standard ClusterIP service for SQL/HTTP client access\n- `StatefulSet/crdb-cluster` — 3 replicas, `podManagementPolicy: Parallel` so all pods start concurrently (avoiding the init deadlock)\n- `PodDisruptionBudget/crdb-cluster-pdb` — `minAvailable: 2` to preserve quorum during voluntary disruptions\n- 3x `PersistentVolumeClaim` — `datadir-crdb-cluster-{0,1,2}`, each 10Gi, all Bound\n\n**Key design notes:**\n- `podManagementPolicy: Parallel` was required because the default `OrderedReady` creates a deadlock: pod-0 can't pass the readiness probe until the cluster is initialized, but init requires all 3 nodes to be up\n- The readiness probe uses `/health` (not `/health?ready=1`) so pods become Ready once the HTTP server is listening, before `cockroach init` is run\n- Each node advertises itself by its full DNS name (`$(hostname -f)` → `crdb-cluster-N.crdb-cluster.cockroachdb.svc.cluster.local`) and joins all 3 peers at startup"}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":492,"cache_read_input_tokens":35100,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":492},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"c53298a9-31cb-4521-9a59-72bab993213d","uuid":"af6a16f7-f507-4e4b-87d8-080d3d3a7b31","request_id":"req_011CcLUTQYzVd9RS3vc1Vopx"}
